      "span_text": "Although the origin of spontaneously damaged p53 À/À polyploids is unknown, one possibility is that they arise from cells that undergo mitotic slippage after mitotic arrest, for example because of the appearance of spontaneous spindle defects, which we earlier observed at low frequency in HCT116 cells [CITATION_1] ."
